tices, Alekna weaves together both rural and urban history to tell the story of the rise of mass society through the lens of communication techniques and technology, showing how the news revolution fundamentally reordered the political geography of China.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aPress and politicszChinaxHistoryy20th century2DLC. 0aRadio broadcastingxPolitical aspectszChinaxHistoryy20th century2DLC. 0aRadio journalismxPolitical aspectszChinaxHistoryy20th century2DLC. 7aHISTORY / Asia / China.2bisacsh  aBroadcasting.  aChina.  aMass politics.  aMedia History.  aNews.  aTechnology.  aTwentieth-Century Politics.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363858740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503638587423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503638587/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles